This paper is primarily focused on the networking aspects of IoT and LTE cellular networks, which falls under the category of Networked and Distributed Systems (cs.NI). The paper also utilizes mathematical modeling and analysis techniques, which could potentially fall under Information Theory (cs.IT) or Systems and Control (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper discusses the potential impact of IoT traffic on network capacity, which could be relevant to Multimedia (cs.MM) or Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC).
